  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "CEB employees can be reduced by half",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, the Minister of Electricity and Energy, says that the current 26,000 staff of the Ceylon Electricity Board can be reduced by half and the work done by the 4,200 employees of the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation as well as the warehouse terminal can be done by 500 employees.",
        "He says on his Twitter account that this can be done by increasing the efficiency of workers and that trade unions grow because of inefficient workers.",
        "He says that although the Ceylon Electricity Board, the Petroleum Corporation and the Petroleum Bulk Storage Terminal have efficient employees, the majority are inefficient.",
        "He says that all government enterprises should be restructured and these institutions have fallen down due to inefficiency, political decisions, political appointments, inefficient administration.",
        "He further says that it is necessary to give merit pay in the public sector as well."
      ],
